 "isNoLongerOnline": false, "latestLaunch": {"id": "1031958", "scheduledAt": "2025-11-28T00:01:00-08:00", "__typename": "Post"}}, {"id": "1114564", "slug": "scorecard", "name": "Scorecard", "tagline": "Evaluate, Optimize, and Ship AI Agents", "logoUuid": "d10b83e0-3372-40a9-8584-d0ca7188e132.png", "reviewsRating": 5.0, "reviewsCount": 1, "categories": [{"id": "1157", "name": "AI Metrics and Evaluation", "slug": "ai-metrics-and-evaluation", "path": "/categories/ai-metrics-and-evaluation", "__typename": "ProductCategory"}, {"id": "1420", "name": "Observability tools", "slug": "observability-tools", "path": "/categories/observability-tools", "__typename": "ProductCategory"}, {"id": "1789", "name": "Prompt Engineering Tools", "slug": "prompt-engineering-tools", "path": "/categories/prompt-engineering-tools", "__typename": "ProductCategory"}], "tags": ["productivity", "developer tools", "artificial intelligence", "ai metrics and evaluation", "observability tools", "prompt engineering tools"], "embeddingSummary": null, "isTopProduct": false, "badges": {"edges": [{"node": {"id": "7283933", "post": {"id": "1023985", "slug": "scorecard-2", "name": "Scorecard", "product": {"id": "1114564", "slug": "scorecard", "__typename": "Product"}, "redirectToProduct": {"id": "1114564", "slug": "scorecard", "__typename": "Product"}, "__typename": "Post"}, "position": 1, "period": "daily", "date": "2025-10-17", "__typename": "TopPostBadge"}, "__typename": "BadgeEdge"}], "__typename": "Connection"}, "followersCount": 543, "isSubscribed": false, "__typename": "Product", "isNoLongerOnline": false, "latestLaunch": {"id": "1023985", "scheduledAt": "2025-10-17T00:01:00-07:00", "__typename": "Post"}}], "__typename": "ProductsSummary"}, "recentLaunches": {"totalCount": 409, "__typename": "ProductsConnection"}, "questions": [], "discussions": {"edges": [{"node": {"id": "800141", "pageViewsCount": 54, "slug": "what-s-your-prompt-engineering-workflow", "createdAt": "2026-01-10T05:39:42-08:00", "path": "/p/vibecoding/what-s-your-prompt-engineering-workflow", "title": "What's your prompt engineering workflow?", "descriptionPreview": "<p>Hey makers! <br>I've been deep in prompt engineering lately while building an AI tool, and I'm genuinely curious about how others approach this. <br>A few questions: <br>1. Do you save your best prompts somewhere? Notion, text files, dedicated app, or just copy-paste from chat history? <br>2. How do you iterate? Do you have a systematic approach or just tweak until it works? <br>3. Different prompts for different models? Or do you use the same prompt for ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini? <br>4. Text vs image prompts do you treat them completely differently? <br>I've noticed I was doing the same optimizations over and over (adding role, being more specific, structuring output format), which made me wonder if everyone has their own \"prompt formula.\" <br>Would love to hear your workflows! </p>", "featuredAt": null, "pinned": false, "user": {"id": "9089781", "name": "Ilia Ilinskii", "username": "ilia_ilinskii", "avatarUrl": "https://ph-avatars.imgix.net/9089781/8f0d2794-e4fa-46d9-b19a-cf26d44dc97b.jpeg", "__typename": "User", "isAccountVerified": false, "isAmbassador": false, "selectedBylineProduct": null, "topProductBadge": null, "topHunterBadge": null, "topLaunchBadge": null}, "hasVoted": false, "votesCount": 7, "__typename": "DiscussionThread", "commentsCount": 5, "featuredComment": null, "primaryForum": {"id": "472520", "slug": "vibecoding", "subject": {"id": "201", "name": "Vibecoding", "thumbnailUuid": "379b8fc1-a8e0-48f3-be0c-15e11b165944.svg", "__typename": "DiscussionCategory"}, "__typename": "DiscussionForumType"}}, "__typename": "DiscussionThreadEdge"}, {"node": {"id": "724866", "pageViewsCount": 290, "slug": "prompting-resources-and-tips", "createdAt": "2025-07-17T06:10:24-07:00", "path": "/p/hugging-face/prompting-resources-and-tips", "title": "Prompting Resources and Tips", "descriptionPreview": "<p>I recently found a dataset on @Hugging Face that has a huge list of prompts. It's called awesome-chatgpt-prompts, but they point out that it's applicable to other models as well. There are some really useful ones in it along with some funny ones like Magician and Lunatic </p><p></p><p>I've found persona prompts like this to be really helpful, and I want to start trying out some of these now. I've even gotten my wife to start using some persona prompts in @ChatGPT by OpenAI and she's getting better results.</p><p></p>", "featuredAt": null, "pinned": false, "user": {"id": "294167", "name": "Jake Crump", "username": "jakecrump", "avatarUrl": "https://ph-avatars.imgix.net/294167/original.jpeg", "__typename": "User", "isAccountVerified": true, "isAmbassador": false, "selectedBylineProduct": {"id": "112572", "name": "Product Hunt", "slug": "producthunt", "logoUuid": "d618ea86-70ae-4d12-8ec2-0ed78c723ddf.png", "isNoLongerOnline": false, "__typename": "Product"}, "topProductBadge": null, "topHunterBadge": null, "topLaunchBadge": null}, "hasVoted": false, "votesCount": 16, "__typename": "DiscussionThread", "commentsCount": 12, "featuredComment": null, "primaryForum": {"id": "29072", "slug": "hugging-face", "subject": {"id": "110569", "name": "Hugging Face", "logoUuid": "b2de76c7-180d-42ca-892c-e360ad7b8771.svg", "__typename": "Product"}, "__typename": "DiscussionForumType"}}, "__typename": "DiscussionThreadEdge"}, {"node": {"id": "727032", "pageViewsCount": 1438, "slug": "prompt-recipes-from-boilerplate-to-production", "createdAt": "2025-07-23T00:00:00-07:00", "path": "/p/vibecoding/prompt-recipes-from-boilerplate-to-production", "title": "Prompt recipes: from boilerplate to production", "descriptionPreview": "<p>AI coding is pretty mindblowing but sometimes it's a headache built on a mountain of bugs. Usually that comes down to issues with how you prompt. So, with that in mind, I'm starting a crowdsourcing discussion so we can all improve our prompts and in turn our apps. </p><p></p><p>Share the exact prompts that turn blank AI requests into real world code. Show us how you go from generate a REST API to a deployable service in just a few steps.</p><p>What to post:</p>", "featuredAt": "2025-07-23", "pinned": false, "user": {"id": "726999", "name": "Aaron O'Leary", "username": "aaronoleary", "avatarUrl": "https://ph-avatars.imgix.net/726999/17085108-59fb-4cb7-8d9e-91a0c10cc14f.jpeg", "__typename": "User", "isAccountVerified": true, "isAmbassador": false, "selectedBylineProduct": {"id": "112572", "name": "Product Hunt", "slug": "producthunt", "logoUuid": "d618ea86-70ae-4d12-8ec2-0ed78c723ddf.png", "isNoLongerOnline": false, "__typename": "Product"}, "topProductBadge": null, "topHunterBadge": null, "topLaunchBadge": null}, "hasVoted": false, "votesCount": 27, "__typename": "DiscussionThread", "commentsCount": 13, "featuredComment": null, "primaryForum": {"id": "472520", "slug": "vibecoding", "subject": {"id": "201", "name": "Vibecoding", "thumbnailUuid": "379b8fc1-a8e0-48f3-be0c-15e11b165944.svg", "__typename": "DiscussionCategory"}, "__typename": "DiscussionForumType"}}, "__typename": "DiscussionThreadEdge"}, {"node": {"id": "697199", "pageViewsCount": 231, "slug": "i-have-some-prompt-tips-to-share", "createdAt": "2025-05-06T03:30:11-07:00", "path": "/p/trickle-3/i-have-some-prompt-tips-to-share", "title": " I have some prompt tips to share", "descriptionPreview": "<p>Prompting is everything in the age of vibe coding. Knowing how to guide AI precisely and efficiently is the key to getting the results you want. Today, I m sharing some of my favorite prompting tips, plus a handy cheatsheet I put together.</p><p></p><p>Prompting Tips That Actually Work</p><ul>\n<li><p>Be spatially specific. Use keywords like \"left\", \"right\", \"centered\", \"aligned to bottom\", \"spaced evenly\" to help the model place elements correctly.</p></li>\n<li><p>Mention device behavior. If it should behave differently on mobile vs desktop, say so. Ex: \"stacks on mobile, grid on desktop\".</p></li>\n<li><p>Use visual vocabulary. Mention familiar UI terms like \"modal\", \"toast\", \"card\", \"hero section\", or \"split view\" to tap into known design structures.</p></li>\n<li><p>Give UX intent. Add the why: \"Add white space for readability\", \"Add a hover effect for feedback\", \"Use a progress bar to show completion\".</p></li>\n<li><p>Sequence your ideas. For complex prompts, list in steps: \"First, add a header. Below that, place a form with two inputs...\". AI loves structure.</p></li>\n<li><p>Say what not to do. If you want to avoid scrollbars, animations, shadows, etc., say so.</p></li>\n<li><p>Don t forget empty states. Great design considers what happens when nothing is there say \"show a placeholder when list is empty\".</p></li>\n<li><p>Test prompt variants. Swap words like \"tile\" vs \"card\", \"modal\" vs \"popup\" to see which gives cleaner structure.</p></li>\n<li><p>Use active voice. Start with a verb: \"Add\", \"Place\", \"Make\", \"Create\", \"Animate\", \"Style\". It helps guide generation.</p></li>\n</ul>", "featuredAt": null, "pinned": false, "user": {"id": "3848136", "name": "Min Zhou", "username": "min_zhou", "avatarUrl": "https://ph-avatars.imgix.net/3848136/94ee6d0b-0f1f-4436-aa94-f132a4c9343e.gif", "__typename": "User", "isAccountVerified": false, "isAmbassador": false, "selectedBylineProduct": {"id": "490060", "name": "Trickle", "slug": "trickle-3", "logoUuid": "2bf153ae-395e-47d2-8787-5970d4f879f9.gif", "isNoLongerOnline": false, "__typename": "Product"}, "topProductBadge": null, "topHunterBadge": null, "topLaunchBadge": null}, "hasVoted": false, "votesCount": 47, "__typename": "DiscussionThread", "commentsCount": 13, "featuredComment": null, "primaryForum": {"id": "40603", "slug": "trickle-3", "subject": {"id": "490060", "name": "Trickle", "logoUuid": "2bf153ae-395e-47d2-8787-5970d4f879f9.gif", "__typename": "Product"}, "__typename": "DiscussionForumType"}}, "__typename": "DiscussionThreadEdge"}], "pageInfo": {"hasNextPage": true, "__typename": "PageInfo"}, "__typename": "DiscussionThreadConnection"}, "relevantReviews": {"edges": [], "__typename": "ProductCategoryRelevantReviewConnection"}}}}